  "summary": "Typosquat of @solana/web3.js exfiltrates host metadata via postinstall script",
  "details": "Package name impersonates the legitimate @solana/web3.js library under a similar-looking scope (@solana-labs). package.json declares a postinstall hook (\"postinstall\": \"node install.js\") that fires automatically on `npm install`. install.js gathers host identifiers (hostname references at lines 10, 35, 37) and uses curl plus an HTTP POST (lines 56, 116) to ship the collected data off-host. This combination — squatted scope + automatic install hook + host-info collection + outbound POST — is the canonical install-time exfiltration pattern.",
